title: Nightly rustc crashes with "unexpected region in query response"

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-stable
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from one stable version to another.

labels.name: A-impl-trait
labels.description: Area: impl Trait. Universally / existentially quantified anonymous types with static dispatch.

body:
Update: Reduced test case in [below comment](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/57464#issuecomment-465791003)

----

Just got this rustc crash in [`juniper_hyper`](https://github.com/graphql-rust/juniper/tree/master/juniper_hyper) in [CI](https://dev.azure.com/graphql-rust/GraphQL%20Rust/_build/results?buildId=162) running `cargo test`:

```
error: internal compiler error: src/librustc/infer/canonical/canonicalizer.rs:194: unexpected region in query response: `ReScope(Node(238))`
2019-01-09T07:10:29.1360436Z 
2019-01-09T07:10:29.1361373Z thread 'rustc' panicked at 'Box<Any>', src/librustc_errors/lib.rs:590:9
2019-01-09T07:10:29.5952924Z note: rustc 1.33.0-nightly (d22fa2d87 2019-01-08) running on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu
2019-01-09T07:10:29.5952971Z 
2019-01-09T07:10:29.5953221Z note: compiler flags: -C debuginfo=2 -C incremental
```
